Topic: Syllogism
1ï¸âƒ£ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

Syllogism questions contain:

2 or more statements

2 or more conclusions

You must decide which conclusions logically follow

ğŸ‘‰ It is based on:

All

Some

No

Railway exams mostly test:

Basic logic

Venn diagram method

Possibility cases

2ï¸âƒ£ Important Rules (Very Important)
ğŸ”¹ ALL (A-type)

â€œAll A are Bâ€

Draw A completely inside B

Conversion: Some B are A

ğŸ”¹ NO (E-type)

â€œNo A is Bâ€

Draw A and B separate

Conversion: No B is A

ğŸ”¹ SOME (I-type)

â€œSome A are Bâ€

Draw overlap

Conversion: Some B are A

ğŸ”¹ SOME NOT (O-type)

â€œSome A are not Bâ€

Partial outside

ğŸ§  Golden Rules (Railway Favourite)

Two negative statements â†’ No conclusion

If one statement is negative â†’ conclusion must be negative

From two universal statements â†’ no particular conclusion

â€œSomeâ€ does NOT mean â€œAllâ€

3ï¸âƒ£ Standard Pattern Example

Statements:

All dogs are animals

All animals are living beings

Conclusion:
â†’ All dogs are living beings âœ…

